      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are accurately identifying a central tension in this debate: a strictly defined Harm Principle creates a very narrow scope for permissible regulation. If the state is limited only to preventing immediate physical violence or illegal incitement, then regulations governing content, like misinformation or harassment, easily slide into viewpoint control. This pushes the philosophical conclusion toward a maximalist defense of free expression, viewing any content-based rule as inherently dangerous government overreach.",
